The '''Shola Ruins''', also known as the '''Shola Catacombs''',<ref name="Mission">{{TORcite|type=crewskill|Archaeology|Fall of the Catacombs}}</ref> were mysterious ruins and deep crevasses which were mostly unexplorable due to the volatile [[Atmosphere/Legends|atmosphere]], [[Groundquake/Legends|groundquakes]], and heavy [[Magma/Legends|magma]] flows native to [[Shola/Legends|Shola]]. Research from deep scans indicated that these caverns included mining tunnel systems which ran all the way down to the core, which would indicate that the [[Extinct Shola species|one-time inhabitants]] of the [[Volcano/Legends|volcanic]] [[Planet/Legends|world]] had dug all the way to the core and caused the [[Destruction of Shola|massive catalysm]] that left the planet in its current state of tectonic and climatic unrest.

==History==
During the [[Cold War (Galactic Republic–Sith Empire)|Cold War]], [[Mining/Legends|mining]] teams of the [[Exchange]] dug periliously close to the famed ruins which put them into a danger of collapsing.<ref name="Mission" />

